1
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,320
I'm going back to sleep.

2
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,080
Let's go grab some breakfast.

3
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,320
I'm not going.

4
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,400
You guys go ahead.

5
00:01:49,479 --> 00:01:52,520
This perfectly good morning was ruined by this time traveler.

6
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:53,720
Speechless.

7
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,220
You're up early today.

8
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:06,200
It's been so many years, I'm used to it.

9
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:09,039
I saw you watching TV until late last night.

10
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:09,680
Yeah.

11
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:12,160
I was too excited last night.

12
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:13,760
Song Yao.

13
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,320
I saw on TV yesterday

14
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:18,520
that advanced technologies in China are everywhere now.

15
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,840
This is what China has achieved continuously

16
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,300
over the past few decades.

17
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:25,120
But during this process,

18
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:28,120
we also went through many bitter experiences.

19
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:31,520
You could say we endured humiliation to bear a heavy burden.

20
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,720
Didn't we win?

21
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,140
Why do we still have to endure humiliation if we won?

22
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,079
We did win,

23
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:41,780
but winning doesn't mean others won't bully you again.

24
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,920
Maintaining peace requires strength.

25
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,960
The invisible smoke of gunpowder

26
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,890
is no less than a real battlefield.

27
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:01,660
Is there anything crueler than bleeding and sacrificing?

28
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,640
And it's right beside us.

29
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,000
What do you mean?

30
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,960
In the past, we resisted foreign aggression.

31
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,960
Now we have a strong military.

32
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:17,240
Education, technology, and the economy,

33
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,120
we must make breakthroughs in everything.

34
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,320
What's more terrifying is

35
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:24,320
they want to use cultural invasion to brainwash today's young people.

36
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,880
So we must defend,

37
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,010
and even fight back.

38
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,520
At first, we chose to endure.

39
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,440
Why endure?

40
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,060
Only by enduring what others cannot,

41
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,560
just like enduring hardships to achieve an ambition.

42
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,480
Not only that.

43
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,240
To develop,

44
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,570
we must also be capable.

45
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,600
Capable,

46
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:49,120
relying on ourselves

47
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:51,050
without depending on anyone else.

48
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,800
Without a strong foundation,

49
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,520
where would this stability come from?

50
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,320
Most of the time,

51
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,960
it's the country silently supporting everything behind the scenes.

52
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,360
We just don't know it.

53
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,200
You're right.

54
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:02,640
In Nanyang,

55
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:07,400
there are many compatriots from different parts of the country.

56
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:10,130
They all went to Nanyang to work hard for a living.

57
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:11,680
Right.

58
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:16,860
Just like venturing to Guandong, going to Xikou, and heading to Nanyang in the past.

59
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:19,120
As our culture goes overseas,

60
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,600
gradually,

61
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:23,480
more and more people will understand our maritime culture.

62
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,810
Just like the Silk Road.

63
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,280
And the Maritime Silk Road.

64
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,480
You even know about the Maritime Silk Road?

65
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,960
Isn't this what your current promotional posters say?

66
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,490
Those are advertisements.

67
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,280
In Nanyang,

68
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:39,640
Grandpa used to often tell me the story of Zheng He's voyages to the Western Seas.

69
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,000
Right.

70
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,280
I was just about to say,

71
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:44,500
China has a long history of oceanic communication.

72
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,060
According to Grandpa,

73
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:51,159
the ships going out to sea back then were fully loaded with all kinds of rare treasures.

74
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,720
I didn't expect what you learned back then

75
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,800
to be the same as what I'm learning now.

76
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,600
This is cultural inheritance.

77
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,400
Our ancestors' shipbuilding abilities

78
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,060
were already world-leading.

79
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,880
We were based on mutual communication

80
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,810
and the goal of common prosperity.

81
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,600
But the ships built by invaders

82
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,520
were loaded with cannons and shells.

83
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,560
Their purpose was colonization

84
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,520
and invasion.

85
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,040
They wanted to destroy China with cannonballs

86
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:16,000
and even reduce us to a colony.

87
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,680
The nature of these ships

88
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,680
is evident in what they are called.

89
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,880
One is a merchant ship,

90
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,760
and the other is an invading warship.

91
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,320
We offered them an olive branch,

92
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:29,850
but they pulled out a dagger behind our backs.

93
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,200
The century of humiliation has long become history.

94
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,159
Today's China

95
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:35,600
is confident

96
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,760
and strong,

97
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:39,159
but still friendly.

98
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:41,159
Therefore,

99
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:44,780
a strong nation is the foundation of peace and prosperity.

100
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,060
Don't underestimate Japan at that time.

101
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,400
In 1942 alone,

102
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,480
it took them only half a year

103
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:56,040
to sweep across most of Asia and the Pacific.

104
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:57,800
In the Far East,

105
00:05:57,800 --> 00:06:00,330
only China was still resisting the invasion.

106
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,840
We defeated the Japanese invaders

107
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:05,170
and overthrew the three great mountains.

108
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:08,980
This was bought with the lives of countless people.

109
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,560
For this moment,

110
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,820
the Chinese people spent over a century.

111
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,200
However,

112
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:22,000
some people still choose to accept their fate.

113
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Accept your fate?

114
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,760
If you accept your fate, you will never stand straight.

115
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:26,960
Not just you,

116
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:29,360
but your descendants too.

117
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,000
So we must unite

118
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,060
and face the outside world together.

119
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,480
Under the call of the Southseas Relief General Association,

120
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,880
11 million overseas Chinese

121
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,040
donated money and goods,

122
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,159
single-mindedly saving the country

123
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:39,840
as one.

124
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,520
It can be said

125
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,340
that it is unprecedented.

126
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,600
This is the gene carved into the bones of the Chinese people.

127
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,440
It is the cohesion of overseas Chinese.

128
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:50,640
This is the cohesion of China.
